title: Com Hem - Wikipedia
snippet: Founded in 1983 as Televerket Kabel-TV as part of the former state-owned Televerket, the company was successively named Svenska Kabel-TV AB and Telia InfoMedia TeleVision AB, before becoming 'Com Hem' (a play on the Swedish phrase Kom hem, "come home") in 1999.

title: Tele2 - Wikipedia
snippet: Tele2 started in 1981 as a mobile phone provider called Comvik as an alternative mobile phone operator to the state-owned company Televerket (today known as Telia Company). The cable television provider Kabelvision AB started in 1986.

title: Tele2 and Com Hem merger - Tele2
snippet: Com Hem Holding was dissolved and all of its assets and liabilities were transferred to Tele2.

title: The merger between Tele2 and Com Hem is completed - Tele2
